2a) Having easy access to the entire history of a file can make someone a more efficient programmer in the long term by allowing them to have more frequent access to changes made in the past. 
 b) As a programmer, someone would want to have a version of their code saved at regular intervals to ensure their work is being saved as they progress. This way, there is a greater chance none of their work will be deleted or get lost.
 c) The importance of commit messages is to allow communication between team members. Also, it allows members to see the history of a project and identify when and why changes were made.
